title: Sweetmeat Glass, 1986-61-246, ca. 1800–20
provenance: Maureen Thompson, London; 1980 Phelps Warren, NY
description: Deep flute-shaped bowl, short tapered stem, slightly domed 8-sided foot; lip scalloped with fan cutting, below that cut drapery swags with narrow vertical flutes above and wider flutes below, foot cut with facets at edges
